Prerequisites
=============
1. Create 2n+1 VMs along with external ip and 2 additional disks as 10Gib & 10Gib
             - data disk
             - zklogs disk
2. Create firewall rule

Documentation to install Kafka and Zookeeper step by step procedure:
====================================================================
SSH as a root user in every VM and process the implementation.
1.	 Update and install java
○	sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install openjdk-8-jdk
2.	Create kafka-startup-script.sh file
●	vi kafka-startup-script.sh
○	sudo mkfs.ext4 -m 0 -F -E lazy_itable_init=0,lazy_journal_init=0,discard /dev/sdb
○	sudo mkfs.ext4 -m 0 -F -E lazy_itable_init=0,lazy_journal_init=0,discard /dev/sdc
○	sudo mkdir -p /mnt/disks/data
○	sudo mkdir -p /mnt/disks/zk-logs
○	sudo mount -o discard,defaults /dev/sdb /mnt/disks/data
○	sudo mount -o discard,defaults /dev/sdc /mnt/disks/zk-logs
○	sudo cp /etc/fstab /etc/fstab.backup
○	echo UUID=$(sudo blkid -s UUID -o value /dev/sdb) /mnt/disks/data ext4 discard,defaults,nofail 0 2 | sudo tee -a /etc/fstab
○	echo UUID=$(sudo blkid -s UUID -o value /dev/sdc) /mnt/disks/zk-logs ext4 discard,defaults,nofail 0 2 | sudo tee -a /etc/fstab

●	chmod +x kafka-startup-script.sh
3.	Create kafka-install.sh file
○	    vi kafka-install.sh
○	    chmod +x kafka-install.sh
         4.   Start the zookeeper and kafka
●	sudo systemctl enable zookeeper.service
●	sudo systemctl enable kafka.service

        5.  Create a jmxremote.password file.
●	    cd /opt/kafka
●	    vi jmxremote.password
●	    monitorRole tenfold                # paste it in the file

       6.  change permissions of  jmxremote.password file.
●	    chown kafka:kafka jmxremote.password
●	    chmod 600 jmxremote.password

      7. add ip and hostname
●	    # added ips host-names at bottom of file.
●	    vi /etc/hosts
 			<internal-IPn> <hostname-n>             # paste all IP-addr and hostnames in the file
●	    source ~/.bashrc                                                     # Refresh the resources


   8. check and update file if anything miss
cat /opt/kafka/config/server.properties
        broker.id=0                                            		 	# Where id= 0,1,...
        broker.rack=zone                                 		 # add zone if it is not there
        listeners=PLAINTEXT://:9092
        advertised.listeners=PLAINTEXT://<Internal-ip>:9092     # add Internal Ip add if not there
        zookeeper.connect=<host-names:port-adds>               	 # add host-nm and port-add of all vms 
        num.network.threads=16
        num.io.threads=8
        socket.send.buffer.bytes=102400
        socket.receive.buffer.bytes=102400
        socket.request.max.bytes=104857600
        log.dirs=/var/log/kafka
        num.partitions=3
        num.recovery.threads.per.data.dir=1
        log.retention.hours=168
        log.segment.bytes=1073741824
        log.retention.check.interval.ms=300000
        zookeeper.connection.timeout.ms=6000
        delete.topic.enable=true
        auto.create.topics.enable=true
        default.replication.factor=3
        num.replica.fetchers=4
        log.message.timestamp.type=LogAppendTime



9. Start and check status of zookeeper and kafka
    systemctl daemon-reload
s-1:
    systemctl start zookeeper.service
    systemctl status zookeeper.service
s-2:
    systemctl start kafka.service
     systemctl status kafka.service
s-3:
     systemctl restart zookeeper.service
    systemctl restart kafka.service

 10. Create and Test the topic
# Create topic
./bin/kafka-topics.sh --create --topic <topic-name> --partitions 3 --zookeeper <host-name:2181> --replication-factor 3

# Describe partitions, replication, leader brokers for selected topic
./bin/kafka-topics.sh --describe --zookeeper <host-name:2181> --topic <topic-name>
	
	# To push messages into topic
	./bin/kafka-console-producer.sh --broker-list  hostname/internal-ip:9092 --topic topic-name

	# To retrieve messages from the topic 
	./bin/kafka-console-consumer.sh --zookeeper hostname/internal-ip:2181 --topic topic-name --from-beginning

